fwprop.note:
Action_1: initialize all period counters
and repetition counters to zero; initialize
all checking status to UNCHECKED; and
set index i to zero (index i iterates over all
all Parameter Monitors in the PMDL)

fwprop.entryDesc:
Execute Monitor Procedure and 
store its return value in monPrRetVal

Increment period counter
of i-th Parameter Monitor

fwprop.note:
The period counter and the
period of a Parameter Monitor
are stored in the monitor's
attributes 'per' and 'perCnt'

The Monitoring Function Procedure is executed cyclically by the host application when the parameter
moniotring function is enabled. It processes all Parameter Monitors in the Parameter Monitoring Lists (PMDL).

Repetiton counter and repetition number 
are stored in attributes repCnt and repNmb

Flag_1 is true if previous and current return
values of monitor procedure are equal

A parameter is valid if data
item valDataItemId masked with 
valMask is equal to valExpVal

fwprop.entryDesc:
Set repetition counter to zero
and checking status to INVALID

fwprop.note:
Flag_2 is true if repetition counter and repetition
number are equal and the return value of the 
Monitor Procedure is different from the monitor's
Checking Status (stored in attribute checkStatus)

fwprop.entryDesc:
Increment repetiion counter
with saturation at the repetiion number

Set checking status equal to
return value of monitor procedure,
add an entry in Check Transition List,
notify functional monitors to whcih the
parameter monitor belongs and run
the CTL Processing Procedure

fwprop.note:
The current and previous return values of
the Monitor Procedure are stored in attributes
monPrPrevRetVal and monPrRetVal

fwprop.entryDesc:
Generate Pre-Defined
Event associated to par. monitor

fwprop.note:
Flag_3 is true if the parameter monitor has an
associated event to report a monitoring violation

fwprop.guardDesc:
The i-th Parameter
Monitor is disabled

Period counter of i-th Parameter
Monitor is smaller than its Period

All parameter monitors in PMDL
have been processed
